{% extends '::base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}ComPPI - Help/ComPPI Species{% endblock %}

{% block bundlecontent %}
	<h1><ul class="NavMenu"><li><a href="{{ path('ComppiDescriptionBundle_help') }}">Help</a></li><li>ComPPI Species</li></ul></h1>

	<br/>
	<p>The ComPPI database contains data for the following species:</p>
	<p></p>
	<ul>
		<li><i>Saccharomyces cerevisiae</i> (Baker's yeast) - (taxonomy ID: <a href="http://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/4932">4932</a>)</li>
		<li><i>Caenorhabditis elegans</i> - (taxonomy ID: <a href="http://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/6239">6239</a>)</li>
		<li><i>Drosophila melanogaster</i> (Fruit fly) - (taxonomy ID: <a href="http://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/7227">7227</a>)</li>
		<li><i>Homo sapiens</i> (Human) - (taxonomy ID: <a href="http://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/9606">9606</a>)</li>
	</ul>
	<p></p>
	<p>On the <a href="{{ path('DownloadCenterBundle_downloads') }}">Downloads</a> page the predefined datasets are available for the four species (<a href="{{ path('ComppiDescriptionBundle_help') }}/downloads">Details</a> and <a href="{{ path('ComppiDescriptionBundle_help') }}/tutorial#download">Tutorial</a>).
	Cross-species comparison of the compartmentalized protein-protein interaction data allows the user to design interactome based evolutionary studies.</p>
	
	<p class="backToTOC"><a href="{{ path('ComppiDescriptionBundle_help') }}">&#x21e6; Back to Help Table of Contents</a>
